{"accepted":[{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Full solution.","id":"vf_7fd2ddbcd4a252cb","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1092: declared status 'disproved'. Formalized: yes. Let $f_r(n)$ be maximal such that, if a graph $G$ has the property that every subgraph $H$ on $m$ vertices is the union of a graph with chromatic number $r$ and a graph with $\\leq f_r(m)$ edges, then $G$ has chromatic number $\\leq r+1$.\n\nIs it true that $f_2(n) \\gg n$? More generally, is $f_r(n)\\gg_r n$? Current best: Tang notes in the comments that a construction of R\\\"{o}dl \\cite{Ro82} disproves the first question, so that $f_2(n)\\not\\gg n$. Prize: no. Tags: chromatic number, geometry.","id":"vf_92584a831abf2d9f","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos1092.f_asymptotic_general https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos1092.f_asymptotic_general.","id":"vf_d49ee72affd73bcb","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1092.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_7fd2ddbcd4a252cb","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1092","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_92584a831abf2d9f","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1092","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_d49ee72affd73bcb","source_root":"sha256